---
source: tests/cli.rs
expression: stdout
---
CLI tool for interacting with reMarkable 2 tablet over SSH

Usage: remarkable-cli [OPTIONS] <COMMAND>

Commands:
  connect   Test connectivity and print device info
  ls        List folder contents
  info      Show full metadata for a document or folder
  find      Search documents by name pattern
  backup    Backup tablet data to local directory
  download  Download a document from the tablet
  upload    Upload PDF or ePub files to tablet
  mv        Move document/folder to a different parent
  mkdir     Create folder(s) on the tablet
  rename    Rename a document or folder
  rm        Delete documents/folders (soft delete by default)
  help      Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)

Options:
      --host <host>          Tablet IP/hostname [auto-discover if omitted]
      --port <port>          SSH port [default: 22]
      --user <user>          SSH username [default: root]
      --password <password>  SSH password (or set `REMARKABLE_PASSWORD` env var) [env: REMARKABLE_PASSWORD=]
      --key_file <key_file>  SSH private key path [default: ~/.ssh/id_rsa]
      --format <format>      Output format [default: human] [possible values: human, json]
      --timeout <timeout>    SSH connection timeout in seconds [default: 5]
      --data_dir <data_dir>  Remote xochitl data directory path [default: /home/root/.local/share/remarkable/xochitl]
      --no-restart           Skip xochitl restart after mutating operations
      --verbose              Enable verbose/debug logging to stderr
      --quiet                Suppress all stderr output
  -h, --help                 Print help
  -V, --version              Print version
